			<p>Dear PINGO user,</p>
		<p>

			recently we have set up a new infrastructure for PINGO in a new data center. <i style="background-color: #B2DFEE;">During the upcoming weekend  (11th/12th) we will migrate the PINGO servers</i> and shut down the old ones.</p>
		<p>

			Due to technical reasons, while migrating you still might reach the “old” servers. In this case, you will be redirected to our new servers being also available at "pingo.cc". We have setup this extra domain to <i style="background-color: #B2DFEE;">keep PINGO live and running during the migration.</i></p>
		<p>

			As a result of the migration to the new data center, we will run PINGO redundantly to minimize failures or downtime. Also, the new infrastructure enables us to to privide enough computing power for the future.</p>
		<p>

			You can get more current news via our newsletter (signup, if you haven’t already, at <a href="https://pingo.upb.de/users/edit">pingo.upb.de/users/edit</a>) or in our (German) <a href="http://blogs.upb.de/pingo">blog</a>.</p>
			
		

